OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,413,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41221
SC,0021
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1778746039
OL,3,CMaternity care of 1,000+ NHS Sussex
OL,4,Ccases to be reviewed following baby
OL,5,Cdeaths
OL,7,F"We welcome Donna Ockenden's review
OL,8,Fand remain committed to fully
OL,9,Fsupporting the process so families can
OL,10,Fget the answers they need, and we take
OL,11,Fany possible opportunity to learn and
OL,12,Fimprove.
OL,14,F"Our overriding priority is always to
OL,15,Fprovide the safest possible care for
OL,16,Fmothers and babies ` that is why our
OL,17,Fmaternity teams have implemented many
OL,18,Fpositive changes in recent years, and
OL,19,Fwhy we will work with the review team
OL,20,Fto find new ways of making our
OL,21,Fservices better, and safer, still."
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}  G21/24
